tus/2055749277268222423/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "medium": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}, "small": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2055749273686249472", "indices": [276, 299], "media_key": "3_2055749273686249472", "media_results": {"result": {"media_key": "3_2055749273686249472"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HId9EpVWEAAmx1y.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 1869, "w": 3338, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 1872, "w": 1872, "x": 1317, "y": 0}, {"h": 1872, "w": 1642, "x": 1432, "y": 0}, {"h": 1872, "w": 936, "x": 1785, "y": 0}, {"h": 1872, "w": 3338, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 1872, "width": 3338}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 1149, "resize": "fit", "w": 2048}, "medium": {"h": 673, "resize": "fit", "w": 1200}, "small": {"h": 381, "resize": "fit", "w": 680}, "thumb": {"h": 150, "resize": "crop", "w": 150}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/zEkld6bgns"}]}, "favorite_count": 2, "favorited": false, "full_text": "AI’s Connectivity Revolution Is Here — And It’s All About Photonics!  Gemini Trading just dropped a crystal-clear infographic that maps exactly how next-gen AI computing clusters are breaking through the electrical bottleneck.  From massive GPU server farms (1) to high-speed https://t.co/zEkld6bgns", "id_str": "2055749277268222423", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "possibly_sensitive": false, "possibly_sensitive_editable": true, "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 0, "retweet_count": 0, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "2429939833"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [{"indices": [1624, 1628], "text": "CPO"}, {"indices": [1629, 1639], "text": "Photonics"}, {"indices": [1640, 1643], "text": "AI"}, {"indices": [1644, 1655], "text": "DataCenter"}, {"indices": [1656, 1671], "text": "Semiconductors"}, {"indices": [1672, 1687], "text": "TechInnovation"}, {"indices": [1688, 1702], "text": "GeminiTrading"}], "symbols": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": [{"id_str": "61559439", "indices": [1604, 1611], "name": "NVIDIA", "screen_name": "NVIDIA"}, {"id_str": "338504881", "indices": [1613, 1622], "name": "Broadcom", "screen_name": "Broadcom"}]}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNTU3NDkyNzcwNTQzNzc5ODQ=", "text": "AI’s Connectivity Revolution Is Here — And It’s All About Photonics!  Gemini Trading just dropped a crystal-clear infographic that maps exactly how next-gen AI computing clusters are breaking through the electrical bottleneck.  From massive GPU server farms (1) to high-speed SerDes links on PCBs (2), traditional copper can’t keep up with exploding bandwidth demands. Enter the star of the show: Co-Packaged Optics (CPO) (3). By integrating Laser and Photonic Integrated Circuit (PIC) directly beside the Switch ASIC, CPO slashes electrical travel distance, cuts power loss, and delivers ultra-low latency at insane speeds.  Compare that to legacy pluggable optical modules (4) — bulkier, hotter, and less efficient. Then watch the magic happen in (5): fiber links extend connectivity from inside the rack (<2 m) across racks (2–30 m), floors (30 m–2 km), and even global data centers (2 km–2000+ km).  The bottom panel perfectly visualizes the E-O-E journey: electrical signals → light via laser → optical fiber → back to electrical. Short-range stays electric; long-haul goes photonic. Result? Dramatically lower energy use, higher bandwidth, and sustainable scaling for trillion-parameter AI models.  This isn’t hype — it’s the infrastructure upgrade the entire AI industry needs. Hyperscalers, chip designers, and data-center operators are already racing toward CPO adoption.  At Gemini Trading we track these photonics breakthroughs because they don’t just move data — they move markets.  What’s your take? Will CPO become the new standard in 2026–2027? Drop your thoughts below!   @GeminiTrading
 @NVIDIA
 @Broadcom

